HEADWORD: Self-renunciation
<hw>Self`-re*nun`ci*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act
of renouncing, or setting aside, one's own wishes, claims, etc.;
self-sacrifice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

